<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2010/07/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>MegaForm.Oqtane</id>
    <version>1.7.46</version>
    <authors>MegaForm Team</authors>
    <owners>MegaForm</owners>
    <title>MegaForm - Dynamic Form Builder</title>
    <description>Dynamic Form Builder for Oqtane — drag-and-drop form designer with templates, multi-step forms, conditional logic, payment widgets, rules engine, and submissions management.</description>
    <copyright>MegaForm Team</copyright>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <license type="expression">MIT</license>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/nicknguyen-oqtane/MegaForm</projectUrl>
    <icon>icon.png</icon>
    <tags>oqtane module form builder survey payment</tags>
    <releaseNotes>v1.7.46 (20260702) — (1) FIX duplicate footer buttons on premium-native shells (euro-youth/intake/down-under/festa/bulgaria): the shell renders its own Back/Next/Submit AND the generic renderer injected .mf-form-actions → two "Next"/"Submit" buttons. Now hidden deterministically from first paint via CSS keyed on the always-set .mf-premium-native-mode wrapper class (also removes the generic-actions flash). (2) Inspector colour rows get a curated COLOUR PALETTE popover (swatch grid + recent + native custom picker) instead of just the OS picker. AssetVersion→20260702-B343. Carries v1.7.45.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.45 (20260702) — Theme Designer (builder Design tab): (1) removed the unfinished/unused LEFT-rail Elements + Colors tabs (only Presets remains). (2) Typography font dropdowns now have a clearly visible border + chevron (was near-invisible #e2e8f0 and could be overridden by the host Bootstrap .form-control). (3) The CSS element picker moved from the (removed) left Colors tab to the RIGHT-rail Inspector sub-tab and was FIXED to actually work: it silently did nothing because (a) the pick-result event was dispatched non-bubbling on document but the panel listens on window, and (b) the iframe applied edits as plain inline style which premium template CSS (!important) overrode. Now: Pick element → the picked element's CSS lists on the right with per-property inputs + colour swatches, and edits apply live to the preview (inline !important). AssetVersion→20260702-B342. Carries all v1.7.44 fixes.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.40 (20260701) — ⭐CRITICAL DEPLOY FIX: the Oqtane ModuleDefinition.Version was frozen at "1.7.15" across every release, so Oqtane treated each new package as "already installed" and NEVER replaced the module DLLs on upgrade (only wwwroot updated) — every C# fix since 1.7.15 silently failed to deploy on existing sites. Bumped ModuleDefinition.Version to 1.7.40 (+ ReleaseVersions) so upgrades actually swap the DLLs. This finally deploys the v1.7.38 i18n Save fix + v1.7.39 template-seed and dashboard bloat-guard on upgraded sites. (1) FIX empty Business Starters / Template Gallery on a CLEAN install: the premium starter templates were only read from App_Data/MegaForm/Templates, which the NuGet never populated → BuilderTemplateCatalogService now SEEDS App_Data from the shipped wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/Templates copy on first run (5 premium templates now ship in the package). (2) FIX "Dashboard shows no forms" on a fresh site: an AI form with a QRCode field holding a 1.5MB base64 logo produced a 3MB schema; rendering it inline as a Blazor MarkupString threw "Unexpected end of input" in insertMarkup and ABORTED the whole page render, so the dashboard's form-list load never ran. Added a ~700KB size guard on the inline schema preload + SSR fields body — oversized forms fall back to the client fetch/render instead of crashing. Carries v1.7.38 i18n Save fix.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.38 (20260701) — ⭐FIX Language Manager "Save" not persisting: the i18n Get endpoint read js/bundles/i18n (shipped defaults) BEFORE js/builder/i18n (author overrides written by i18n/save). Since the package ships every locale in bundles/i18n, saved/AI-translated strings were shadowed → "Save" appeared to do nothing on reload. GetI18nLocale now reads builder/i18n (overrides) first. AssetVersion unchanged (server-side fix). Carries v1.7.37 Content-Slider editor fix.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.37 (20260701) — ⭐FIX Content Slider editor regression: the packaged wwwroot shipped a STALE content-slider widget plugin (js/plugins/megaform-widget-content-slider.js, old 20KB from 06-17) instead of the 06-28 redesign (42KB, Overlay/Card/Cards templates + Ken Burns + drag-follow) → installing overwrote the live plugin with the old one → the rich "Open Slider Designer" modal was missing. Rebuilt the plugin from source (tsc plugins/tsconfig) and synced to the package wwwroot. AssetVersion→20260701-B341. Carries v1.7.36 Import-JSON fix.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.36 (20260701) — ⭐FIX Wizard Import-JSON: (1) the DEPLOYED default templates put customHtml/customCss at the TOP LEVEL (not inside settings) → wizardTemplateFromJson now merges top-level custom* into settings so premium templates import WITH their shell (was silently downgraded to a plain standard form). (2) Import was silent (a valid file only changed the off-screen name field → felt like nothing happened) → now shows a toast "Imported \"…\" — N fields loaded", and JSON/parse errors surface as toasts instead of alert(). +4 wiz.import_* keys (de/vi). AssetVersion→20260701-B340. Carries v1.7.35 Wizard i18n.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.35 (20260701) — ⭐Form Wizard i18n: the wizard shell, step-nav, Setup step and Template-Gallery/Import-JSON modal are now keyed under wiz.* (46 keys) with German + Vietnamese translations shipped and English placeholders for the rest (fill via the in-product "Translate (AI)" tool). I18N_CACHE_VERSION bumped so stale locale caches drop. AssetVersion→20260701-B339. Carries v1.7.34.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.34 (20260701) — ⭐NEW option-icon PALETTE (pick emoji + MegaForm icon catalog for Chips/Cards option icons, no more raw typing) + FIX euro-youth stray 1px card border above the stepper (CustomShellCompatibilityCssService NOINNER now recognizes the nested .ey-card so the transparent outer .mfp stays borderless) + Form Wizard entry paths: a Template Gallery browse modal (category + search + preview) and Import-JSON, parallel to starting from scratch. Complete language packs (38 locales). AssetVersion→20260701-B338.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.33 (20260626) — ⭐FIX AI multi-step + AI form polish: (1) AI multi-step forms always showed an EMPTY first page — a page-break Section on the FIRST field made calculatePages() emit an empty leading page; it now only starts a new page when the current page has content (leading/consecutive page breaks no longer create blank pages). (2) Step labels are now derived from the actual page structure (fieldPages) — the leading section names step 1 correctly instead of a generic off-by-one "Step 1". (3) Multi-step (standard) forms dropped the gray --mf-page-bg wrapper frame ("card thừa bên ngoài") via .mf-form-wrapper:has(.mf-steps) so the white card sits on the page, consistent with the frameless single-page AI forms. (4) AI pure-grid (custom-shell) forms had ~36px DOUBLE field spacing (per-field margin-bottom STACKED on the container flex gap) — .mfp .mf-field-group margin-bottom:0 lets the shell gap own spacing (→16px). AssetVersion→20260626-B287. Includes v1.7.32 builder template-gallery regression fixes.
    PREVIOUS v1.7.32 (20260626) — ⭐FIX builder template-gallery regressions (Oqtane fullscreen): (1) "Template Preview" pane was BLANK — the loader's inline live-form suppressor (scan()) cloaked the in-memory preview .mf-form-wrapper because the preview modal is a body-level [data-mf-overlay] OUTSIDE the builder root; scan() now skips wrappers inside [data-mf-overlay]. (2) "Upload Template" file dialog didn't open for users on a stale cached builder.js — the loader's BUILDER_BUNDLE_VERSION was a HARDCODED constant ('20260626-B244') that never busted the cache when builder.js was rebuilt; it now derives from the loader's own ?v (= AssetVersion), so one AssetVersion bump busts loader + builder + builder CSS together. AssetVersion→20260626-B284. Includes v1.7.31 — ⭐COMPLETE LANGUAGE PACKS + drift guard. Fixed incomplete i18n in the package: js/plugins/i18n was stale (1189 keys) and top-level js/i18n was absent — both now carry the full canonical catalog (1268 keys × 18 locales), matching js/builder/i18n + js/bundles/i18n. Root cause: pack.cmd never ran the i18n platform-sync, so the wwwroot wildcard shipped partial packs. Fix is permanent: i18n-sync-platforms.cjs now covers all four Oqtane i18n dirs (auto-creating missing ones), and pack.cmd runs it + a verify-package-complete.cjs guard that ABORTS the pack if any i18n/KB directory is incomplete. KB (34 TemplateGuides .md + 8 PromptRecipes via wwwroot, ai-knowledge-seed.json + RazorWidgets embedded in the DLLs) and SQL (EF migrations in the Server DLL) verified complete. AssetVersion→20260626-B283. Carries v1.7.30 settings-popup trim + v1.7.29 i18n/popup. dropped the redundant subtitle line, the duplicate inner "Module form" label (the accordion header already says it), and the clean-state "Active preset: …" line (dupe of the header meta). AssetVersion→20260626-B282 (cache-bust). Builds on v1.7.29 — ⭐SETTINGS PANE: i18n + POPUP. The in-page ⚙ Settings UI (Module form / Theme &amp; Layout / Theme preset / Layout / Page integration) is now (1) fully localized — ~67 new vd.set.* keys wired through the runtime catalog with REAL translations for all 11 maintained locales + Vietnamese (was 100% hardcoded English), and (2) opens as a TRUE centered popup with a dim backdrop instead of an inline pane. Also closed the i18n drift gate: +12 missing subs.* "Send to Inbox" keys added + translated (gate back to PASS). Inherits v1.7.28 clean-host install fix (all MF_* tables created on a fresh host).</releaseNotes>
    <summary>Dynamic form builder module for Oqtane CMS</summary>

    <packageTypes>
      <!-- "Dependency" is the standard NuGet library type — confirmed working by CISS.SideMenu reference -->
      <packageType name="Dependency" />
      <!-- Oqtane.Framework: minimum compatible framework version — read by InstallationManager XPath -->
      <packageType name="Oqtane.Framework" version="6.1.2" />
    </packageTypes>

    <dependencies>
      <group targetFramework="net9.0" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         COMPLETENESS (verified in v1.7.27): this package is COMPLETE for a clean Oqtane install —
         · DLLs: all MegaForm assemblies (Client/Server/Shared/Core/Sdk) + non-host deps
           (Newtonsoft.Json, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language, Microsoft.CodeAnalysis[.CSharp]),
           for BOTH net9.0 and net10.0 (entries below).
         · KBs / SQL scripts: the wwwroot wildcard ships all KB content under
           wwwroot\Modules\MegaForm\Resources\ (34 TemplateGuide .md + PromptRecipes) + all js/css/
           fonts/img. The MF_* table "SQL scripts" are the EF migrations COMPILED INTO the Server DLL
           (Migrations\*.cs + EntityBuilders) — not standalone files — so they ship inside lib\*.
         ⭐ For a COMPLETE build, run the full `pack.cmd` (it npm-builds the 7 JS bundles + Vite-syncs
            them into MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\wwwroot BEFORE packing). A lean re-pack only refreshes
            what's already in that wwwroot — stale/missing bundles there → an incomplete package.
         ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- net9.0 builds -->

    <!-- Client Blazor WASM DLL — tên chứa "Oqtane" → được load bởi IsOqtaneAssembly() -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Server DLL — tên chứa "Oqtane" → được load -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Shared DLL — tên chứa "Oqtane" → được load -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Core DLL — tên KHÔNG chứa "Oqtane" → KHÔNG được load vào AppDomain -->
    <!-- Nhưng vẫn cần trong bin/ vì Client/Server DLL có reference đến nó -->
    <!-- .NET runtime sẽ tự resolve khi cần (dependency resolution) -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Core.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- Third-party dependencies not provided by Oqtane host -->
    <!-- Newtonsoft.Json is used by MegaForm.Core; Oqtane 6 does NOT ship it -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Newtonsoft.Json.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <!-- [pkg-fix 20260625] MegaForm runtime deps the Oqtane host does NOT provide. Without these a
         CLEAN-host install crashes at startup (ReflectionTypeLoadException during Oqtane's assembly
         scan): MegaForm.Sdk → Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language → Roslyn (CodeAnalysis). The
         :5070 dev site only worked because it had accumulated them from earlier manual deploys. -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\MegaForm.Sdk.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net9.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.dll" target="lib\net9.0" />

    <!-- net10.0 builds (Oqtane 10.x hosts, e.g. :5070 Oqtane.MSSQL3 + :5000 Oqtane.New10) -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Client.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Oqtane.Shared.Oqtane.pdb" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Core.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\Newtonsoft.Json.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\MegaForm.Sdk.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.Language.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\bin\Release\net10.0\Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.dll" target="lib\net10.0" />

    <!-- FIX 3: wwwroot — path đúng: wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/** → deploy vào {webroot}/Modules/MegaForm/ -->
    <!-- Oqtane extract: bỏ 1 segment "wwwroot" → còn Modules/MegaForm/... → vào wwwroot/Modules/MegaForm/ -->
    <file src="..\MegaForm.Oqtane.Server\wwwroot\Modules\MegaForm\**\*.*" target="wwwroot\Modules\MegaForm" />

    <!-- Package metadata -->
    <file src="icon.png" target="" />
    <file src="license.txt" target="" />
    <!-- Note: license.lic under wwwroot\Modules\MegaForm\ is already packed by the
         wildcard above (**\*.*). Do NOT add an explicit entry here — NuGet will
         throw NU5050 (duplicate destination). -->
  </files>
</package>
